  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tbsp of olive oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add katsuramuki-cut bell peppers and cook for 4 minutes. Add onion and cook for 3 minutes. Add garlic and cook for 1 minute. Add poblano peppers and cook for 3 minutes. Add ground cumin, smoked paprika, and a pinch of salt and pepper.",
    "Stir in ricotta cheese and cook for 1-2 minutes, until slightly melted and creamy. Taste and adjust seasoning as needed. Stir in chopped cilantro.",
    "Warm mini-cocottes by placing them in the oven for 2-3 minutes at 375°F. Fill each mini-cocotte with the fajita mixture and serve immediately."
